# {{project_name}}

Upload images to R2 (Cloudflare's object storage). PNG, JPEG, WebP, GIF, SVG. 10MB cap.

## One-time R2 bucket setup

The wizard scaffolds the wrangler binding, but R2 buckets must exist before the Worker can write to them. Either:

- Cloudflare Studio → R2 → **+ New bucket** → name it `{{project_name}}-uploads`
- Or: `pnpm exec wrangler r2 bucket create {{project_name}}-uploads`

Then redeploy this project.

## Endpoints

```
POST /upload        — multipart/form-data with "file"   → { key, url }
GET  /:key          — fetch by key (with cache headers)
GET  /list          — list uploaded objects
DELETE /:key        — delete
```

## Upload from an HTML form

```html
<form action="https://YOUR-WORKER-URL/upload" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
  <input type="file" name="file" accept="image/*" required />
  <button>Upload</button>
</form>
```

Or from JS:
```js
const fd = new FormData();
fd.append("file", fileFromInput);
const { url } = await fetch("https://YOUR-WORKER-URL/upload", { method: "POST", body: fd }).then(r => r.json());
```
